# ─── Build-time env (committed template) ────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to .env (and optionally .env.production / .env.staging / .env.development).
# build.sh loads the environment-specific file, falling back to .env, and exports
# every key into process.env.
#
# Build-time injection into the backend bundle is OPT-IN via a leading underscore:
#   _FOO=...   → esbuild bakes the literal value in, replacing `process.env._FOO`.
#                Use for secrets / values fixed at build time.
#   FOO=...    → runtime-only; never baked into the backend bundle.
# So adding a plain key to .env can never silently end up hard-coded in the bundle.
#
# The webview (vite) is a separate channel — it bakes in only VITE_ / CCG_PUBLIC_
# keys, which ARE exposed to end-user browsers. Never give a secret a VITE_ /
# CCG_PUBLIC_ prefix. A `_`-prefixed secret is safe: vite ignores it, so it never
# reaches the webview bundle.
#
# See docs/build-env-injection.md for the full model.

# Telemetry (Rybbit) API key — backend only, baked in at build time (`_` = bake-in).
_CCG_RYBBIT_API_KEY=

# Example public webview flag (prefixed → exposed to the browser):
# CCG_PUBLIC_EXAMPLE_FLAG=true
